 book contains essays on the notion of theory from the Greeks and the early German Romantics to the contemporary use of this notion in literary studies. The last part of the book investigates the different ways of understanding philosophical thinking that are found in contemporary French thought, examining works of Foucault, Deleuze, Lyotard, and Derrida.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Methodology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362602740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626027423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626027/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles